    "The imbalance in the training set may lead to less prediction power for less-characterized BGC types.",
    "Lastly, there is no universally accepted approach for constructing negative samples (non-BGC sequences) for training.",
    "Ideally, the negative samples should resemble true BGCs while avoiding false positives.",
    "The arbitrarily constructed negative samples may also affect the model performance.",
    "Addressing these issues of data limitation is crucial for advancing AI-driven BGC discovery and ensuring more accurate and robust predictions across diverse BGC classes."
  ],
